paragraphs.title: Download the dataset
paragraphs.text:
%sh
# Download 
cd /data
if [[ ! -f covtype.data.gz ]]
then
    echo "Downloading covtype.data.gz"
    curl --silent -O https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/covtype/covtype.data.gz
fi

paragraphs.title: Read the dataset
paragraphs.text:
%spark
// Specify path to downloaded log file
// Note that Spark is able to read directly gzipped files
val datasetPath = "/data/covtype.data.gz"

val dataset = spark.read.
 option("inferSchema", true).
 option("header", false).
 csv(datasetPath)

 "Elevation", "Aspect", "Slope",

 ) ++ (
 (0 until 4).map(i => s"Wilderness_Area_$i")

 (0 until 40).map(i => s"Soil_Type_$i")
 ) ++ Seq("Cover_Type")
 
val data = dataset.toDF(colNames:_*).withColumn("Cover_Type", $"Cover_Type".cast("double"))

paragraphs.title: Vectorize datas
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.VectorAssembler

val inputCols = trainData.columns.filter(_ != "Cover_Type")
val assembler = new VectorAssembler().setInputCols(inputCols).setOutputCol("featureVector")
val assembledTrainData = assembler.transform(trainData)

assembledTrainData.select("featureVector").show(truncate = false)

paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.classification.RandomForestClassifier
import scala.util.Random

val classifier = new RandomForestClassifier()
 .setSeed(Random.nextLong())
 .setLabelCol("Cover_Type")
 .setFeaturesCol("featureVector")
 .setPredictionCol("prediction")
 
val model = classifier.fit(assembledTrainData)

println(model.toDebugString)

def unencodeOneHot(data: DataFrame): DataFrame = {
 val wildernessCols = (0 until 4).map(i => s"Wilderness_Area_$i").toArray

 val soilAssembler = new VectorAssembler().setInputCols(soilCols).setOutputCol("soil")
 
 soilAssembler.transform(withWilderness).drop(soilCols:_*).withColumn("soil", unhotUDF($"soil"))
}
